ikor.collection
Interface MutableDictionary<K,V>

All Superinterfaces:
Collection<K>, Dictionary<K,V>, java.lang.Iterable<K>, MutableCollection<K>, java.io.Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
DynamicDictionary
public interface MutableDictionary<K,V>
extends Dictionary<K,V>, MutableCollection<K>

Mutable collection interface. In contrast to the standard Java Collections Framework, mutable collections are separated from the standard immutable collection interface (as in COCOA for Mac OS X and iOS).

Author:
Fernando Berzal (berzal@acm.org)
